Class CommandVerifierType

  • java.lang.Object

  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    MetaCommandType.VerifierSet.AcceptedVerifier, MetaCommandType.VerifierSet.CompleteVerifier, MetaCommandType.VerifierSet.ExecutionVerifier, MetaCommandType.VerifierSet.QueuedVerifier, MetaCommandType.VerifierSet.ReceivedVerifier, MetaCommandType.VerifierSet.SentFromRangeVerifier, MetaCommandType.VerifierSet.TransferredToRangeVerifier

    public class CommandVerifierType
extends OptionalNameDescriptionType
    A command verifier is used to check that the command has been successfully executed. Command Verifiers may be either a Custom Algorithm or a Boolean Check or the presence of a Container for a relative change in the value of a Parameter. The CheckWindow is a time period where the verification must test true to pass.
